Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Line a #baking sheet{} with foil and lightly oil. Wash and dry all produce.

Core, deseed, and dice @green bell pepper{1}(cored and diced) into ¾-inch pieces. Toss on one side of prepared #sheet{} with a drizzle of oil, @Southwest spice blend{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. (You'll use the remaining Southwest Spice in the next step.)

Place @butter{1%tbsp} in a medium #microwave-safe bowl{}; microwave until melted, ~{30%seconds}. Stir in @panko breadcrumbs{1/2%cup}, @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup}, @Southwest spice blend{2%tsp}(remaining), salt, and pepper.

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup}, and a pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with salt and pepper. Place on opposite side of sheet from bell pepper. Spread half the @sour cream{2%tbsp} (you'll use the rest in the next step) onto tops of chicken. Mound with panko mixture, pressing to adhere (no need to coat the undersides).

Bake on middle rack until chicken is cooked through, crust is golden, and bell pepper is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Meanwhile, finely dice @Roma tomato{1}(finely diced). Trim and finely chop @scallions{2}(trimmed and chopped). Zest and quarter @lime{1} (for 4 servings, zest and halve 1 lime; quarter remaining lime).

In a second medium #bowl{}, combine tomato, scallions, juice from half the lime (both lime halves for 4), and a pinch of salt.

In a #small bowl{}, combine remaining @sour cream{2%tbsp}, a pinch of lime zest, a squeeze of lime juice, and a pinch of salt. Add @water{1%tsp} 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in roasted bell pepper, @butter{1%tbsp}, and remaining lime zest to taste. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice and crispy crust chicken between plates. Top with salsa fresca and drizzle with lime crema. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Crispy chicken is always a recipe for success. Add melty Monterey Jack cheese and bold spices to the mix, and you've got a winning dinner. Once baked, the crust turns golden brown while the meat stays juicy and tender. Together, with bell-pepper-studded rice and tangy lime crema, it's a meal as elegant as it is satisfying and delicious.